The default JRE provides an XML parser: the Apache Xerces!
So, when you run your code, instead of picking up the eXML parser, the JVM finds first the one provided in the boot classpath: the Apache Xerces (org.apache.crimson)...

To solve this issue, you have 2 options:
1- You run your code against a JRE which has not a predefined XML parser. For example, the JCL Foundation, and you add eXML to your classpath!

2- JAXP apis let you set two system properties:
    - "javax.xml.parsers.SAXParserFactory": to reassign the default SAX Parser factory to another factory.
    - "javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilderFactory": to reassign the default DOM Builder factory to another factory.

In this case, you run your code against your current JRE but:
a/ Before calling the SAXParserFactory.newInstance() api, you set the system property "javax.xml.parsers.SAXParserFactory" to "org.eclipse.ercp.jaxp.implForCore.SAXParserFactoryImpl"
or
b/ Before calling the DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance(), you set the system property "javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilderFactory" to "org.eclipse.ercp.jaxp.implForCore.DocumentBuilderFactoryImpl"

Here are the 2 different ways of setting the System properties and instanciating the parser:
=======================
System.setProperty(
         "javax.xml.parsers.SAXParserFactory",
         "org.eclipse.ercp.jaxp.implForCore.SAXParserFactoryImpl");
SAXParserFactory factory1 = SAXParserFactory.newInstance();
System.out.println(factory1);
SAXParser parser = factory1.newSAXParser();
System.out.println(parser);

System.setProperty(
         "javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilderFactory",
         "org.eclipse.ercp.jaxp.implForCore.DocumentBuilderFactoryImpl");
DocumentBuilderFactory factory2 = DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance();
factory2.setExpandEntityReferences(false);
factory2.setIgnoringComments(true);
System.out.println(factory2);
DocumentBuilder builder = factory2.newDocumentBuilder();
System.out.println(builder);
=======================
Running this code, you should obtain the following trace on your console:
=======================
